==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bossy
<hw>Bos"sy</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. fr. Prov. E. <ets>boss</ets>
in <ets>boss-calf</ets>, <ets>buss-calf</ets>, for
<ets>boose-calf</ets>, prop., a calf kept in the stall. See 1st
<er>Boose</er>.]</ety> <def>A cow or calf; -- familiarly so
called.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

